t = \sin x - \cos x
(3-\cos 4x)(\sin x - \cos x)=2.
\sin x - \cos x = \sqrt{2}(\sin(x - \frac{\pi}{4}))
x = y + \frac{\pi}{4}
(3+ \cos(4y))\sin y = \sqrt{2}
\sin y = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
(3+ \cos(4y))\sin y = \sqrt{2}
\sin y
3-\cos 4x > 0
\sin x - \cos x>0
t = \sin x - \cos x = \sqrt{2}\sin\left(x - \dfrac{\pi}{4}\right)
0<t \leqslant \sqrt{2}
t = 1
 t^2 = (\sin x - \cos x)^2  = 1 -\sin 2x.
3 - \cos 4x =3 - (1-2\sin^2 2x )= 2[1-(1-t^2)^2] = 2(t^4 -2t^2 + 2)
2(t^4 -2t^2 + 2)t = 2,
t^5- 2t^3+2t - 1 = 0.
